label: Country
definition: Country in which study was conducted

label: Schistosoma mansoni infection intensity, by microscopy
definition: Schistosoma mansoni infection intensity, in mean eggs per gram (EPG) of feces, from all slides examined for a study participant. Up to three stool samples were collected per participant on consecutive days. A minimum of two slides were prepared from each stool sample using the Kato-Katz method and examined by light microscopy for parasite eggs.
codebookDescription: Eggs per gram (epg) of S. mansoni eggs from all available Kato-Katz (KK) tests for the participant

label: Schistosoma mansoni, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of Schistosoma mansoni infection in a study participant, based on detection of at least one parasite egg in any of the stool samples. Up to three stool samples were collected per participant on consecutive days. A minimum of two slides were prepared from each stool sample using the Kato-Katz method and examined by light microscopy for parasite eggs.
codebookDescription: Binary flag to indicate S. mansoni infection through egg detection in KK

label: Schistosoma haematobium, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of Schistosoma haematobium infection in a study participant, based on detection of at least one parasite egg in any of the urine samples. Up to three urine samples were collected per participant on consecutive days. Urine filtrations were examined by light microscopy for parasite eggs.
codebookDescription: Binary flag to indicate S. haematobium infection through egg detection in urine

label: Schistosoma haematobium infection intensity, by microscopy
definition: Schistosoma haematobium infection intensity, in mean eggs per 10 ml urine, from all slides examined for a study participant. Up to three urine samples were collected per participant on consecutive days. Urine filtrations were examined by light microscopy for parasite eggs.

label: Schistosoma mansoni, by CCA
definition: Presence or absence of Schistosoma mansoni infection in a study participant, based on POC-CCA urine assay
codebookDescription: Binary flag to indicate positive CCA test for S. mansoni

label: Microhematuria
codebookDescription: Binary flag to indicate positive hemastix test
